      "writtenOn": "2016-11-22T17:46:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this field is a bit specific for a generic shader variable.\n\nWhat if we just convert:\n\nsetLayoutQualifier -\u003e addLayoutQualifier(const char* qualifier) {\n    if (!fLayoutQualifiers.isEmpty()) {\n        fLayoutQualifiers.append(\", \");\n    }\n    fLayoutQualifiers.append(qualifier);\n}\n\n(also, layout qualifiers are GLSL specific afaik. Is there a reason they were dropped down into here?)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "9a52a43178bca9482d710fe60def82fe0fa44b4b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d079ec3f_ab2f494f",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrShaderVar.h",
        "patchSetId": 22
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-22T18:07:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m in the process undoing the \"shader/sl\" and \"glsl\" split since with SkSL we don\u0027t really need the split. These Gr-types will really be used to construct sksl code which has layout qualifiers currently. Until yesterday there was a GrGLSLShaderVar that had layout qualifiers but now there is just GrShaderVar.\n\nOn the field, I kind of think this class should become more structured rather than less. That is, I\u0027d support making the existing uses of layout qualifiers and modifiers move towards enums, key value pairs, or something along those lines. If a caller wants to append a bunch of strings together to declare a variable it seems like they don\u0027t need this class which provides inspectability and could be a place to catch contradictory settings. I\u0027m not totally convinced on this but that thinking is was lead me to implementing it the way I did. I\u0027m definitely open to being convinced the other way.\n\nThat said, I do think the constructors and set() methods here could use some cleanup. It\u0027d be OK for the rarely used fields to have explicit standalone setters only.",
      "parentUuid": "d079ec3f_2b62791c",
      "revId": "9a52a43178bca9482d710fe60def82fe0fa44b4b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d079ec3f_ce9743d7",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrShaderVar.h",
        "patchSetId": 22
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-22T18:32:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the long run a think a system where we have specific layout modifiers that we set would work better.  As of now we are already restricted on what layouts qualifiers we can use by what we support in the compiler. If SkSL evolves pass using glsl to describe shaders, I think having a set of \"property\" values that can be set and are supported by the sksl compiler makes the most sense.",
      "parentUuid": "d079ec3f_ab2f494f",
      "revId": "9a52a43178bca9482d710fe60def82fe0fa44b4b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "30324888_f61f8076",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrShaderVar.h",
        "patchSetId": 22
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-22T18:50:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed for sksl.\n\nI guess my main beef with having it as a member of the class is just that the image store format is so specific to such an an uncommon type of variable. It\u0027s unfortunate to tack that onto everything. I also agree that tossing around raw strings defeats the purpose of this class. Maybe we just need real layout qualifier types with key/value pairs, like you suggested.\n\nObviously putting together a system of typed layout qualifiers is out of the scope of this change. So unless we want to implement that first, we need to choose one of those other two options. The rationale for sticking with raw strings still as layout qualifiers would be that it\u0027s correct in terms of optional key/value properties, and we already implement all the other layout qualifiers as raw strings anyway. But I\u0027m fine with either way.\n\nUltimately it would be cool if we could get rid of all this shader glue and link everything together with sksl\u0027s own flavor of optional properties and builtins!",
      "parentUuid": "d079ec3f_ab2f494f",
      "revId": "9a52a43178bca9482d710fe60def82fe0fa44b4b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
